HEADWORD: Underconsumption
<hw>Un`der*con*sump"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Polit.
Econ.)</fld> <def>Consumption of less than is produced; consumption of
less than the usual amount.</def> <rj><au>F. A. Walker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

